.cm
|SHOWME EXEC%
 
    This is an EXEC to show the contents of a user directory entry.
    The user id is displayed in a XEDIT session and allows the
    user to check various things.
 
    When the cursor is put on one of the following items and PF11 is pressed
    a certain action is executed.
 
.cm
  |USER%     - The user id is XAUTOLOGged
  |IDENTITY% - The user id is XAUTOLOGged
  |SUBCONFIG%- The content of the SUBCONFIG is displayed
  |INCLUDE%  - The content of the included PROFILE is displayed
  |IPL%      - If the IPL statement contains a FILEPOOL entry the
  |   %        the filespace for the user is displayed
  |MDISK%    - The content of the MINIDISK is displayed
  |LINK%     - The MINIDISK that is LINKed is displayed
 
.cm
|Notes:%
  |1)%The EXEC depends on the working of DIRMAINT
  |  %or a MONOLITHIC USER DIRECT
  |  %For MONOLITHIC issue GLOBALV SELECT SHOWME SETLP DIRTYPE MONOLITHIC
  |  %For DIRMAINT   issue GLOBALV SELECT SHOWME SETLP DIRTYPE DIRMAINT
  |2)%This requires CP CLASS B for ATTACH/DETACH to the SYSTEM
  |  %              CP CLASS A for DEFINE MDISK and OPTION DEVMAINT
  |  %              in the CP Directory
  |3)%For FILEPOOL actions the invoking id needs FILEPOOL authorisation
  |  %i.e. being PERMITTED to the item or ADMIN authority
  |4)%Parts of this EXEC are EXECLOADED (put into storage/memory)
  |5)%MDISK and LINKs are also displayed when checking
  |  %SUBCONFIG/INCLUDE statements
  |6)%When you EXECLOAD this EXEC with filetype REXX you can use it
  |  %as a PIPE stage
